Yaqi, Richard, Sonny, Joe, Jia, Hridesh, and Earl, hello.
It was wonderful to see you today! I=92m excited that each of you is beginn=
ing to develop your personal portfolio of assets =97 evidence you=92ll use =
to stand out and make yourselves very attractive to future employers and cl=
ients. Alongside your personal portfolios, we=92ll also continue strengthen=
ing our shared community assets that benefit the whole group.
Attached is the form I use to develop TIM projects and check alignment with=
 client needs. It=92s kind of similar to the Supervisor Assignment Request =
(SAR) form. Please use this version to describe your projects. For now, foc=
us only on describing the project itself =97 please don=92t add extra secti=
ons (like the method) just yet.
Keep in mind that every project requires you to do solid research. To do re=
search, you=92ll need at the very least a framework, relevant data, and a c=
lear way to analyze that data. Building these elements carefully will set y=
ou up for success.
I=92m looking forward to seeing how your personal project portfolios take s=
hape! I am here to support you every step of the way.
Warm regards and best wishes.
Tony B.






